Privacy Policy
Effective Date: January 3, 2025
Introduction
Welcome to the Blood Pressure - Blood Sugar app, your trusted companion for monitoring and managing your health metrics with ease. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring the security of the personal data you entrust to us. This Privacy Policy serves as a transparent guide, detailing the types of information we collect, the ways we use this information to enhance your experience, and the measures we take to protect your data. By understanding our practices, you can feel confident that your privacy is respected and your data is handled responsibly while using our app.
Information We Collect
1. Personal Information:
Health and Usage Data: This refers to the health metrics you input, such as blood pressure readings, blood sugar levels, and user preferences. These data points help us provide tailored features, such as tracking trends over time, generating insights, and customizing your app experience based on your individual needs.
Contact Information: This includes any email address or other contact details you provide during using the app, which allows us to communicate with you about any issues requiring assistance.
2. Non-Personal Information:
We may gather details about your interactions with the app, which may include the following:
Device Information: Such as your device model and operating system.
Log Data: Including your IP address, timestamps of access, and the pages or features you view.
App usage analytics, including crash reports and feature interaction.
How We Use Your Information
1. To deliver app functionalities (e.g., health tracking).
2. To optimize app performance and user experience.
3. To send important updates or communications.
4. To conduct research with anonymized data for app enhancements.
5. To fulfill legal requirements and safeguard our rights.
6. To deliver the products and services you have requested.
Information Sharing
1. We do not sell your personal information.
Your privacy is of utmost importance to us. Under no circumstances do we sell, trade, or rent your personal data to third parties for commercial purposes. Your data is exclusively used to enhance your experience with the app and deliver the services you expect.
2. Information may be shared under specific circumstances:
With Trusted Service Providers: We may share certain data with third-party service providers who assist us in analyzing app performance, understanding user behavior, and improving functionality. These providers are bound by strict confidentiality agreements and are only permitted to use your data for the purposes we specify.
To Comply with Legal Obligations or Enforce Terms of Service: In rare cases, we may disclose your information if required by law, such as in response to a court order, subpoena, or other legal processes. Additionally, we may share data to enforce our Terms of Service, protect our rights, or prevent fraud and misuse of the app.
Data Storage and Types of Data
1. Automatic Information Collection
We automatically collect certain information to ensure the smooth operation of the app. This data is used solely for operational purposes, such as improving performance and providing the services you request. We do not retain this information after it is no longer necessary. Once the related services are provided, any automatic information collected will be deleted.
2. Information Provided by Users
Any data you provide, such as health metrics or personal details, is stored only on your device. We do not back up this data on external servers. Should you choose to uninstall the app, all stored data will be irretrievably deleted from your device. You can be assured that no data is retained or transferred after uninstalling the app.
Security Measures
We employ industry-standard security protocols to safeguard your personal data from unauthorized access, loss, or alteration. These measures include encryption, secure communication channels, and access controls to protect your information. However, it’s important to note that while we take every precaution to secure your data, no method of transmission over the internet or storage system is completely immune to risks. As such, we cannot guarantee absolute security, but we are committed to continually improving our security practices to mitigate potential vulnerabilities.
Third-party Partners’ Privacy Policy
Below are links to the privacy policies of our third-party partners. Please be aware that these policies are governed and managed by the respective third parties, and we have no control over their practices. We encourage you to review their privacy policies to understand how they collect, use, and share your data.
