Children's Privacy
The app is not designed for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect, process, or store any personal data from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a child under 13, we will take immediate steps to delete that information from our records. Parents or guardians are encouraged to monitor and control their children's use of the app to ensure compliance with this age restriction.
Your Rights
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
The right to access and obtain a copy of your information
The right to rectify inaccurate or incomplete information
The right to delete your information
The right to restrict or object to processing
The right to data portability
The right to withdraw consent at any time (if processing is based on consent)
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices, services, or legal requirements. When we make significant updates, we will notify you by revising the "Effective Date" at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy regularly to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your data. By continuing to use the app after any updates, you acknowledge and agree to the revised terms.
Contact Us
If you have any concerns regarding your privacy or questions about our practices, please feel free to contact us at
ben.mertyuksel@gmail.com
. We are committed to addressing your concerns and ensuring your data is handled with the utmost care.
